orea -- tThe governance of social investment policies in comparative perspective: long-term care in England and South Korea -- tTowards greater social investments and equality in Europe and East Asia: policies and politics -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSocial investment policies have enjoyed prominence during recent welfare reforms across the OECD world, and yet there is insufficient long-term strategy for their success. Reviewing labour market, family and education policies, this edited collection analyses the emergence of social investment policies in both Europe and East Asia. Adopting a life course perspective and examining both public and private investments, this book addresses key contemporary policy issues including care, learning, work, social mobility and inequalities. Providing original observations, this seminal text explores the roads and barriers towards effective social investment policies, derives practical social policy implications and highlights important lessons for future policymaking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aHuman services. 0aPublic welfare administration. 0aPublic welfarezEast Asia. 0aPublic welfarezEurope. 0aPublic welfare. 0aSocial servicexSocieties, etc. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aAn, Mi Young, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBan, Ga Woon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoi, Hyejin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoi, Young Jun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChung, Heejung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurazzi, Niccolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov